# Machine Learning Notes - Lab 2
## Multiple Variable Linear Regression

---

# Objective

Build a Multiple Variable Linear Regression model from scratch and understand how Gradient Descent learns the best weights (w) and bias (b).

---

# Dataset

Features (X_train)

| House Size | Bedrooms | Floors | Age |
|------------|----------|--------|-----|
|2104|5|1|45|
|1416|3|2|40|
|852|2|1|35|

Target (y_train)

| Price |
|-------|
|460|
|232|
|178|

Shape

```
X_train → (3,4)

3 = Training Examples (Rows)

4 = Features (Columns)
```

```
y_train → (3,)
```

---

# Overall Flow

```
Training Data
      │
      ▼
Predict
      │
      ▼
Compute Cost
      │
      ▼
Compute Gradient
      │
      ▼
Gradient Descent
      │
      ▼
Update w and b
      │
      ▼
Repeat Until Cost is Minimum
```

---

# Important Variables

## X_train

Stores all input features.

Shape

```
(m,n)

m = Number of Training Examples

n = Number of Features
```

Example

```
(3,4)

↓

3 Houses

4 Features
```

---

## y_train

Stores actual target values.

Shape

```
(m,)
```

---

## w (Weights)

Every feature has one weight.

```
Size -----------> w1

Bedrooms -------> w2

Floors ---------> w3

Age ------------> w4
```

Shape

```
(n,)
```

---

## b (Bias)

Single value added after the dot product.

Shape

```
Scalar
```

---

# Function 1 : predict()

Purpose

Predicts the price of ONE training example.

Formula

```
Prediction

=

w·x + b
```

Code

```python
prediction = np.dot(x,w) + b
```

Flow

```
Input Features

↓

Multiply with Weights

↓

Add Everything

↓

Add Bias

↓

Prediction
```

Returns

```
Scalar
```

---

# Function 2 : compute_cost()

Purpose

Measures how wrong the model is.

Formula

```
             m
J = 1/2m Σ (Prediction-Actual)²
            i=1
```

Flow

```
For Every House

↓

Predict

↓

Compare with Actual

↓

Find Error

↓

Square Error

↓

Add Errors

↓

Divide by 2m

↓

Return Cost
```

Lower Cost

↓

Better Model

---

# Why Square the Error?

Example

Prediction

```
460
```

Actual

```
500
```

Error

```
-40
```

Square

```
(-40)^2

=

1600
```

Reasons

✔ Removes negative values

✔ Punishes larger mistakes

---

# Function 3 : compute_gradient()

Purpose

Calculates how every parameter should change.

Returns

```
dj_dw

Gradient of every Weight

dj_db

Gradient of Bias
```

Flow

```
For Every House

↓

Predict

↓

Calculate Error

↓

For Every Feature

↓

Update Gradient

↓

Average Gradient

↓

Return dj_dw and dj_db
```

This function DOES NOT update the weights.

It only calculates the gradients.

---

# Function 4 : gradient_descent()

Purpose

Learns the best values of w and b.

Flow

```
Repeat

↓

Compute Gradient

↓

Update Weight

↓

Update Bias

↓

Compute New Cost

↓

Repeat
```

Update Equations

```
w = w - α × dj_dw

b = b - α × dj_db
```

---

# Learning Rate (α)

Controls step size.

Small α

```
Very Slow Learning
```

Good α

```
Fast Convergence
```

Large α

```
Overshoots

Diverges
```

---

# Cost History

Stores cost after every iteration.

```
J_history
```

Graph

```
Cost

│

│\

│ \

│  \

│   \_____

└────────────

Iterations
```

