# New Terms Learned

### Feature

Input variable.

Example

```
House Size

Bedrooms

Floors

Age
```

---

### Training Example

One complete row of data.

Example

```
[2104,5,1,45]
```

---

### Weight (w)

Importance of every feature.

---

### Bias (b)

Constant added to every prediction.

---

### Prediction

Estimated output.

Formula

```
f(x)=w·x+b
```

---

### Error

Difference between prediction and actual value.

```
Error

=

Prediction

-

Actual
```

---

### Cost Function

Measures the overall error of the model.

---

### Gradient

Direction in which each parameter should move.

---

### Gradient Descent

Optimization algorithm that repeatedly updates w and b until cost becomes minimum.

---

### Learning Rate (α)

Controls how much the parameters change in every iteration.

---

### Iteration

One complete cycle of

```
Predict

↓

Cost

↓

Gradient

↓

Update
```

---

# Key Equations

Prediction

```
f(x)=w·x+b
```

Cost

```
          1
J =  -------- Σ(Prediction-Actual)²
       2m
```

Weight Update

```
w = w - α × dj_dw
```

Bias Update

```
b = b - α × dj_db
```

---

# Final Summary

```
Training Data
      │
      ▼
Prediction
      │
      ▼
Error
      │
      ▼
Cost
      │
      ▼
Gradient
      │
      ▼
Update Weights & Bias
      │
      ▼
Repeat Until Cost is Minimum
```

---

# One Line Summary

```
Predict → Measure Error → Calculate Gradient → Update Parameters → Repeat Until Cost Becomes Minimum.
```